<h1>Bigos (Hunter's Stew) Recipe</h1>

<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
    <li>500g pork shoulder (cubed)</li>
    <li>300g smoked kielbasa sausage (sliced)</li>
    <li>200g bacon (diced)</li>
    <li>300g beef chuck (cubed)</li>
    <li>1 medium onion (chopped)</li>
    <li>3 garlic cloves (minced)</li>
    <li>800g sauerkraut (drained and rinsed)</li>
    <li>1 small head of cabbage (shredded)</li>
    <li>1 cup dried mushrooms (rehydrated in hot water, then chopped)</li>
    <li>1 cup prunes (pitted and chopped)</li>
    <li>1 apple (grated)</li>
    <li>1 cup red wine</li>
    <li>1-2 bay leaves</li>
    <li>1 tbsp caraway seeds</li>
    <li>1 tbsp allspice</li>
    <li>1 tbsp paprika</li>
    <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
    <li>1 tbsp vegetable oil</li>
    <li>500ml beef broth</li>
    <li>Optional: juniper berries for extra flavor</li>
</ul>

<h2>Instructions</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Prepare the Meats:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Heat oil in a large pot. Brown the pork shoulder and beef chuck on all sides, then set aside.</li>
            <li>Add the bacon to the pot and fry until crispy. Remove and set aside with the other meats.</li>
            <li>In the same pot, add the sliced kielbasa sausage and brown. Remove and set aside.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Cook the Onions and Garlic:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Add chopped onion to the pot, saut√© until softened.</li>
            <li>Add minced garlic and cook for another minute.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Add Sauerkraut and Cabbage:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Stir in the sauerkraut and shredded cabbage, mixing well with the onions and garlic. Cook for about 5
                minutes.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Add Mushrooms, Prunes, and Apple:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Stir in the rehydrated mushrooms, chopped prunes, and grated apple.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Return Meats to the Pot:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Add the browned pork, beef, sausage, and bacon back into the pot.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Season and Add Liquids:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Pour in the red wine and beef broth.</li>
            <li>Add the bay leaves, caraway seeds, allspice, and paprika.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add juniper berries if using.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Simmer:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Cover the pot and simmer over low heat for 2-3 hours, stirring occasionally. The longer you cook bigos,
                the better the flavor, so you can let it simmer for up to 4 hours if desired.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Rest and Reheat:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Bigos tastes even better the next day, so it's ideal to let it cool, refrigerate overnight, and reheat
                before serving.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Serve</h2>
<p>Serve hot with a side of rye bread or mashed potatoes.</p>

<p>Enjoy your hearty and flavorful <strong>Bigos</strong>!</p>
